WEBVTT

00:00:00.400 --> 00:00:04.150
Good evening, family. Thank you for

00:00:04.160 --> 00:00:07.269
joining us again tonight. It's Diana and

00:00:07.279 --> 00:00:09.990
Brandon, and we're excited to be here. We

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:11.430
have some things in our heart,

00:00:11.440 --> 00:00:13.830
but I don't have a lot; I'm

00:00:13.840 --> 00:00:15.509
just going to pray with you all. I know we

00:00:15.519 --> 00:00:18.710
came on a little bit later than normal.

00:00:18.720 --> 00:00:23.349
I try to come on by then, but

00:00:23.359 --> 00:00:26.470
as you're driving

00:00:26.480 --> 00:00:28.230
around like we were today, we could

00:00:28.240 --> 00:00:29.589
feel the presence. I told

00:00:29.589 --> 00:00:29.599
Diana,

00:00:29.599 --> 00:00:31.029
'Don't you just feel the presence of the

00:00:31.039 --> 00:00:32.549
Lord so strongly?'And she could, too.

00:00:32.559 --> 00:00:34.310
It was right after we watched Billy

00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:36.870
Burke last night; the presence of the

00:00:36.880 --> 00:00:39.110
Lord was tangible when he was in

00:00:39.120 --> 00:00:40.950
Orlando.

00:00:40.960 --> 00:00:46.069
Truly, I have never experienced

00:00:46.079 --> 00:00:49.670
through a phone or a device

00:00:49.680 --> 00:00:51.430
watching and feeling the presence of the

00:00:51.440 --> 00:00:53.910
Lord fill your car or your house like

00:00:53.920 --> 00:00:58.869
that.

00:00:58.869 --> 00:00:58.879
It

00:00:58.879 --> 00:01:02.630
lingered all night and all day.

00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:04.950
As I was seeking Him and

00:01:04.960 --> 00:01:06.950
as I went to

00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:11.190
the prayer group last night,

00:01:12.960 --> 00:01:14.950
I had an open-eyed

00:01:14.960 --> 00:01:17.510
vision of Jesus.

00:01:17.520 --> 00:01:21.590
He came, and I didn't know that

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:24.469
Diana had been praying for me that

00:01:24.469 --> 00:01:24.479
afternoon.

00:01:24.479 --> 00:01:26.950
After I

00:01:26.960 --> 00:01:28.149
told her what happened, she started

00:01:28.159 --> 00:01:30.310
crying and said, 'Brandon, I was

00:01:30.320 --> 00:01:32.469
interceding for you, just asking God to

00:01:32.479 --> 00:01:34.550
give you a refreshing.

00:01:34.560 --> 00:01:36.390
I know you pour out so much

00:01:36.400 --> 00:01:38.710
and you're tired a lot.'She

00:01:38.710 --> 00:01:38.720
said,

00:01:38.720 --> 00:01:40.550
'I was

00:01:40.550 --> 00:01:40.560
in

00:01:40.560 --> 00:01:43.109
my own private prayer time this

00:01:43.119 --> 00:01:46.469
morning, and I was praying for you. I

00:01:46.479 --> 00:01:48.389
asked the Lord to become real to

00:01:48.389 --> 00:01:48.399
Braden

00:01:48.399 --> 00:01:50.870
even more, help him, and give him

00:01:50.870 --> 00:01:50.880
strength.'When

00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:53.749
I went to

00:01:53.759 --> 00:01:55.830
prayer that night—which was Sunday

00:01:55.840 --> 00:01:57.670
night,

00:01:57.680 --> 00:02:00.870
I

00:02:00.870 --> 00:02:00.880
guess—my

00:02:00.880 --> 00:02:03.990
life just

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:07.830
runs together. Last night, He spoke

00:02:07.840 --> 00:02:10.790
to me, and I said, 'Lord, I miss

00:02:10.790 --> 00:02:10.800
You.'All

00:02:10.800 --> 00:02:12.390
of a sudden, I just

00:02:12.400 --> 00:02:13.990
closed my eyes, and Jesus appeared before

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:15.589
me in a vision, like He does whenever I'm

00:02:15.599 --> 00:02:18.070
on here.

00:02:18.080 --> 00:02:21.430
He started talking to me about some things

00:02:21.440 --> 00:02:24.470
that were very private,

00:02:24.480 --> 00:02:26.309
encouraging me just like she was

00:02:26.319 --> 00:02:28.710
asking. Because of all the things

00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:30.869
that I had delivered this last week, it

00:02:30.879 --> 00:02:32.550
was hard.

00:02:32.550 --> 00:02:32.560
I

00:02:32.560 --> 00:02:34.550
said, 'Lord, I need

00:02:34.560 --> 00:02:37.270
refreshing. Is everything okay? Are we

00:02:37.280 --> 00:02:39.910
cool right

00:02:39.910 --> 00:02:39.920
now?'And

00:02:39.920 --> 00:02:41.910
He said, 'Well,

00:02:41.920 --> 00:02:44.070
why wouldn't it

00:02:44.070 --> 00:02:44.080
be?'I

00:02:44.080 --> 00:02:46.150
said, 'Well,

00:02:46.160 --> 00:02:48.229
I've had a rough week.'And He said,

00:02:48.229 --> 00:02:48.239
'Brandon,

00:02:48.239 --> 00:02:50.869
you just need to be refreshed.

00:02:50.879 --> 00:02:52.229
You're dry. You're

00:02:52.239 --> 00:02:55.589
thirsty.'You

00:02:55.599 --> 00:02:57.270
know, ladies and

00:02:57.280 --> 00:03:01.270
gentlemen, when you are so used to

00:03:01.280 --> 00:03:04.869
going through the valley of life,

00:03:04.879 --> 00:03:07.430
He said, 'Once you pass a certain

00:03:07.430 --> 00:03:07.440
test—Jesus

00:03:07.440 --> 00:03:09.030
said this to me

00:03:09.030 --> 00:03:09.040
yesterday—once

00:03:09.040 --> 00:03:12.390
you pass a certain test

00:03:12.400 --> 00:03:14.149
in school, you don't keep

00:03:14.159 --> 00:03:16.390
going there.

00:03:16.400 --> 00:03:18.309
You

00:03:18.309 --> 00:03:18.319
graduate.'As

00:03:18.319 --> 00:03:21.670
you are in the body of Christ,

00:03:21.680 --> 00:03:24.070
as you are on the potter's

00:03:24.070 --> 00:03:24.080
wheel

00:03:24.080 --> 00:03:26.390
and as you go from

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:29.589
glory to glory, you don't camp in the

00:03:29.599 --> 00:03:31.110
valley.

00:03:31.120 --> 00:03:34.550
You don't camp in what you're

00:03:34.560 --> 00:03:37.589
going through for the refining fire. The

00:03:37.599 --> 00:03:40.789
refining fire is for a season,

00:03:40.799 --> 00:03:43.190
and once you pass the

00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:45.509
test, you don't have to take

00:03:45.509 --> 00:03:45.519
it

00:03:45.519 --> 00:03:47.350
again.

00:03:47.360 --> 00:03:48.949
He said, 'Brandon, you went through

00:03:48.959 --> 00:03:50.789
those things and you passed those tests,

00:03:50.799 --> 00:03:53.110
but you're so used to camping around

00:03:53.120 --> 00:03:55.509
what you had been through in the past.'From

00:03:55.509 --> 00:03:55.519
working

00:03:55.519 --> 00:03:58.229
at my grandmother's,

00:03:58.239 --> 00:04:00.070
working

00:04:00.080 --> 00:04:02.149
at the church, and having Megan,

00:04:08.799 --> 00:04:11.830
you build a wall of defense

00:04:11.830 --> 00:04:11.840
where

00:04:11.840 --> 00:04:14.070
you're always looking

00:04:14.080 --> 00:04:17.110
for the next blow.

00:04:21.519 --> 00:04:23.590
You feel

00:04:23.600 --> 00:04:25.430
that victim mentality where you walk

00:04:25.440 --> 00:04:27.430
through life feeling like you're

00:04:27.440 --> 00:04:29.030
always going through something

00:04:29.040 --> 00:04:30.870
because you're growing

00:04:30.880 --> 00:04:33.510
from glory to glory. But those tests were for

00:04:33.510 --> 00:04:33.520
that season

00:04:33.520 --> 00:04:36.150
of life.

00:04:38.080 --> 00:04:40.550
The Lord says as you

00:04:40.560 --> 00:04:44.230
grow and mature,

00:04:44.240 --> 00:04:47.430
those things

00:04:47.440 --> 00:04:50.390
become the tests that you passed.

00:04:50.400 --> 00:04:52.710
Just like in fifth,

00:04:52.720 --> 00:04:54.310
sixth, or seventh grade, you

00:04:54.320 --> 00:04:55.830
don't go back and repeat those. You just

00:05:00.400 --> 00:05:01.830
take what you learned

00:05:01.830 --> 00:05:01.840
and

00:05:03.270 --> 00:05:03.280
add

00:05:03.280 --> 00:05:05.350
to

00:05:05.360 --> 00:05:08.469
it.

00:05:08.479 --> 00:05:10.550
You keep going

00:05:10.550 --> 00:05:10.560
until

00:05:10.560 --> 00:05:12.390
you graduate.

00:05:12.400 --> 00:05:14.950
You always remember what you

00:05:14.960 --> 00:05:17.590
learned, but you never have to

00:05:17.600 --> 00:05:20.390
take the test that you took to get

00:05:20.400 --> 00:05:22.390
to the next level. You go from glory to

00:05:22.400 --> 00:05:24.870
glory. That's what He was

00:05:24.880 --> 00:05:27.830
showing me: that season

00:05:27.840 --> 00:05:32.550
is done, and He is taking me somewhere new.

00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:34.469
There are seasons of blessing

00:05:34.469 --> 00:05:34.479
and

00:05:34.479 --> 00:05:37.270
refreshing

00:05:37.270 --> 00:05:37.280
in

00:05:37.280 --> 00:05:40.070
every believer's life. It's not

00:05:40.080 --> 00:05:43.110
always about the valley.

00:05:43.120 --> 00:05:44.870
We go through

00:05:44.880 --> 00:05:47.110
hard times

00:05:47.110 --> 00:05:47.120
in

00:05:47.120 --> 00:05:48.629
our Christian walk, and that's what makes us

00:05:48.639 --> 00:05:50.390
stronger.

00:05:50.400 --> 00:05:53.029
Diana found this man who

00:05:53.029 --> 00:05:53.039
had

00:05:53.039 --> 00:05:55.749
died and went to

00:05:55.759 --> 00:05:57.510
heaven.

00:05:57.510 --> 00:05:57.520
In

00:05:57.520 --> 00:05:59.749
his testimony,

00:05:59.759 --> 00:06:02.390
he came back and said his mother told him

00:06:02.400 --> 00:06:05.590
in heaven,

00:06:07.280 --> 00:06:09.189
'Don't forget

00:06:09.199 --> 00:06:11.830
what pain feels like,

00:06:12.080 --> 00:06:13.510
because you won't have any of it up

00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:13.990
here.'Don't

00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:16.870
take it for

00:06:16.880 --> 00:06:17.749
granted.

00:06:20.720 --> 00:06:24.230
Pain causes you to grow;

00:06:24.240 --> 00:06:26.790
trials cause you to grow. There

00:06:26.790 --> 00:06:26.800
are

00:06:26.800 --> 00:06:29.990
no trials up there to

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:34.309
spur you to grow. The hard times

00:06:34.319 --> 00:06:36.710
are what refines you. A lot of times,

00:06:42.479 --> 00:06:44.070
when your flesh is screaming

00:06:44.080 --> 00:06:46.950
the loudest is when God has His hand on

00:06:46.960 --> 00:06:48.870
that potter's wheel and He's pushing down.

00:06:48.880 --> 00:06:52.550
Does God cause the pain? No. I

00:06:52.560 --> 00:06:54.150
want to tell you God is a

00:06:54.160 --> 00:06:55.909
rewarder of those who diligently seek

00:06:55.919 --> 00:06:58.710
Him. He is a blesser, not a

00:06:58.710 --> 00:06:58.720
curser.

00:06:58.720 --> 00:07:01.589
But

00:07:01.599 --> 00:07:02.870
because we live in a fallen world,

00:07:02.880 --> 00:07:04.870
hard times come.

00:07:04.880 --> 00:07:07.189
I

00:07:07.199 --> 00:07:08.870
always stay on God's side;

00:07:08.880 --> 00:07:11.510
God

00:07:11.520 --> 00:07:13.510
does not put sickness on people to teach

00:07:13.510 --> 00:07:13.520
them

00:07:13.520 --> 00:07:15.670
a lesson. I don't believe that.

00:07:15.680 --> 00:07:17.350
There's no sickness in heaven, so how

00:07:17.360 --> 00:07:20.070
can He give it to you? When you get

00:07:20.080 --> 00:07:22.230
to heaven, He doesn't have any sickness

00:07:22.240 --> 00:07:24.070
there, and He and the devil

00:07:24.080 --> 00:07:26.309
aren't buddies joining up

00:07:26.309 --> 00:07:26.319
to

00:07:26.319 --> 00:07:28.469
inflict

00:07:28.469 --> 00:07:28.479
His

00:07:28.479 --> 00:07:30.230
kids. What kind of father would do

00:07:30.240 --> 00:07:32.550
that?

00:07:32.560 --> 00:07:34.950
The Bible

00:07:34.960 --> 00:07:37.110
says, 'If you, being evil, give good gifts

00:07:37.120 --> 00:07:38.629
to your children, how much more does

00:07:38.639 --> 00:07:41.029
your heavenly Father give good gifts to

00:07:41.039 --> 00:07:43.670
those that love Him?'He's not giving

00:07:43.680 --> 00:07:45.189
snakes

00:07:45.189 --> 00:07:45.199
or

00:07:45.199 --> 00:07:47.350
sickness to teach you

00:07:47.360 --> 00:07:48.950
something.

00:07:56.720 --> 00:08:00.309
Because we live in a fallen

00:08:00.319 --> 00:08:02.950
world and go through

00:08:02.960 --> 00:08:04.790
life,

00:08:04.800 --> 00:08:09.990
it molds us and you grow—and

00:08:09.990 --> 00:08:10.000
also because of

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:12.070
our own dumb

00:08:12.080 --> 00:08:13.830
decisions.

00:08:16.479 --> 00:08:18.469
But

00:08:21.990 --> 00:08:22.000
regarding

00:08:26.639 --> 00:08:27.990
the valley,

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:29.589
the man

00:08:36.959 --> 00:08:39.029
said, 'Don't forget the way pain feels

00:08:39.039 --> 00:08:41.589
because you won't feel any in

00:08:41.589 --> 00:08:41.599
heaven.'The

00:08:41.599 --> 00:08:44.070
trial makes you grow.

00:08:44.080 --> 00:08:45.829
She

00:08:45.839 --> 00:08:48.389
said, 'And don't forget what touch

00:08:48.399 --> 00:08:50.310
feels like

00:08:50.320 --> 00:08:52.710
in this way, because it's different in

00:08:52.710 --> 00:08:52.720
heaven.'When

00:08:52.720 --> 00:08:55.670
he went to

00:08:55.670 --> 00:08:55.680
heaven—and

00:08:55.680 --> 00:08:57.670
I know he had an authentic encounter,

00:08:57.680 --> 00:09:00.150
this man wept the whole time—the glory

00:09:00.160 --> 00:09:02.949
of the Lord was present.

00:09:04.959 --> 00:09:08.870
He was a druggie and had a

00:09:08.880 --> 00:09:10.550
massive heart attack,

00:09:12.070 --> 00:09:12.080
and

00:09:13.120 --> 00:09:15.430
when he went up there, he

00:09:15.440 --> 00:09:17.990
had all this about the Father and

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:20.389
all the inadequacies that we

00:09:20.399 --> 00:09:22.470
feel because God is so perfect. But

00:09:22.480 --> 00:09:24.230
every single thing he said was things

00:09:24.240 --> 00:09:27.910
that Jesus had said to me. Every single

00:09:27.910 --> 00:09:27.920
thing,

00:09:27.920 --> 00:09:29.829
not every single thing, but a lot of

00:09:29.839 --> 00:09:31.750
them. I don't, because that's

00:09:31.760 --> 00:09:34.230
exaggeration.

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:36.949
Some of the things he said the Lord

00:09:36.959 --> 00:09:39.269
said to him were what the Lord said to me

00:09:39.279 --> 00:09:41.430
privately in the visitations I've

00:09:41.440 --> 00:09:44.870
had with him, and I thought, he said that to

00:09:44.880 --> 00:09:48.710
him too? Isn't that amazing

00:09:48.710 --> 00:09:48.720
that

00:09:48.720 --> 00:09:50.790
he'll help you through it? That

00:09:50.800 --> 00:09:53.750
you can't mess your life up?

00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:55.829
The footsteps of the righteous are

00:09:55.829 --> 00:09:55.839
ordered

00:09:55.839 --> 00:09:57.670
of the Lord. Brandon, he said that to

00:09:57.680 --> 00:09:59.509
me. The footsteps of the righteous are

00:09:59.519 --> 00:10:01.910
ordered of the Lord. No matter how hard you

00:10:01.920 --> 00:10:03.670
try, you couldn't mess your life up

00:10:03.680 --> 00:10:06.470
if you're seeking me

00:10:06.480 --> 00:10:08.949
and you're looking towards my face. He

00:10:08.959 --> 00:10:10.949
said, You can't mess your life up

00:10:10.959 --> 00:10:12.790
because I'll turn what the devil meant

00:10:12.800 --> 00:10:15.030
for bad and turn it around for good for

00:10:15.040 --> 00:10:16.470
you, Brandon, if you're always looking

00:10:16.480 --> 00:10:18.389
for me.

00:10:18.399 --> 00:10:20.710
No matter how bad you mess your life up,

00:10:20.720 --> 00:10:22.470
how bad you might think you've messed

00:10:22.480 --> 00:10:24.630
your life up, if you're seeking the

00:10:24.640 --> 00:10:28.310
Lord, he'll turn it on a dime. It's

00:10:28.320 --> 00:10:31.190
about putting Jesus first. We must learn

00:10:31.200 --> 00:10:33.910
to put Jesus first.

00:10:33.920 --> 00:10:37.670
He is everything.

00:10:37.680 --> 00:10:39.910
If you put him first in your marriage,

00:10:39.920 --> 00:10:41.990
if you put him first with your children,

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:44.069
if you put him first in your

00:10:44.069 --> 00:10:44.079
finances—that's

00:10:44.079 --> 00:10:45.750
why the Bible says, you know, a

00:10:45.760 --> 00:10:46.949
lot of people get all upset when you

00:10:46.959 --> 00:10:49.269
tell them about tithing and giving, but

00:10:49.279 --> 00:10:52.069
we were forced to learn how to tithe.

00:10:52.079 --> 00:10:54.150
Our church forced us to tithe.

00:10:54.160 --> 00:10:56.470
Because we were on staff,

00:10:56.480 --> 00:10:58.550
if we didn't tithe, they'd fire you. And

00:10:58.560 --> 00:11:01.269
so I knew

00:11:01.279 --> 00:11:02.949
whenever you're forced to learn how to

00:11:02.959 --> 00:11:06.150
tithe, it then becomes habit because

00:11:06.160 --> 00:11:08.949
we worked there for so many years.

00:11:08.959 --> 00:11:10.949
So people say, Oh, I don't believe in

00:11:10.959 --> 00:11:14.310
tithing. Oh, I believe with all my heart.

00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:16.470
I believe in tithing more

00:11:16.470 --> 00:11:16.480
than—I'm

00:11:16.480 --> 00:11:18.389
telling you, I have got the revelation of

00:11:18.399 --> 00:11:20.230
tithing,

00:11:20.240 --> 00:11:22.550
not because of something that I wanted,

00:11:22.560 --> 00:11:24.630
but because I was forced to. And I thank

00:11:24.640 --> 00:11:26.470
God for Mark all the time. Pastor

00:11:26.480 --> 00:11:29.910
Mark, he taught us the

00:11:29.920 --> 00:11:32.389
fundamentals of tithing. It was,

00:11:32.399 --> 00:11:34.230
like I said, strong-armed, but

00:11:34.240 --> 00:11:37.269
I'm thankful that he did it because if

00:11:37.279 --> 00:11:39.269
he wouldn't have done it, I wouldn't

00:11:39.279 --> 00:11:41.430
have got the revelation of it. I was a

00:11:41.440 --> 00:11:44.150
tipper. I was a tipper.

00:11:44.160 --> 00:11:46.069
I'd give God a little bit here and there,

00:11:46.079 --> 00:11:48.310
and

00:11:48.320 --> 00:11:49.910
you give him what you could or

00:11:49.920 --> 00:11:52.790
whatever, whenever it was convenient.

00:11:52.800 --> 00:11:55.590
But as we grew and God

00:11:55.600 --> 00:11:57.350
started speaking to Diana, she got her

00:11:57.360 --> 00:12:00.870
education, her master's degree,

00:12:00.880 --> 00:12:02.790
and did all that through

00:12:02.800 --> 00:12:05.110
her schooling and pushing as

00:12:05.120 --> 00:12:06.790
hard as we did. But then the Lord gave

00:12:06.800 --> 00:12:09.590
us an idea outside of what we naturally

00:12:09.600 --> 00:12:10.710
